str2: A primary particle; but, and, etc.

parse: Verb - Aorist Participle Active - Nominative Masculine Plural
str2: From para and erchomai; to come near or aside, i.e. To approach, go by, perish or neglect, avert.
Mysia, a region of Asia Minor.

parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Active - 3rd Person Plural
str2: To go down, come down, either from the sky or from higher land, descend. From kata and the base of basis; to descend.
A primary preposition; to or into, of place, time, or purpose; also in adverbial phrases.
Troas, a harbor city of Mysia. From Tros; the Troad, i.e. Troas, a place in Asia Minor.
